# User Profile

<!--
This file tells the LLM summarizer who you are, so the daily brief can be written
for you rather than for nobody in particular. `script/setup` copies this file to
`data/user_profile.md` on first run. Edit it there — the real file is gitignored.

Keep it short and concrete. Bullet points work better than paragraphs.
-->

## Current projects
- **project-a** — short description of what it is and why you care about news on it.
- **project-b** — another one.

## Priority topics
- Topic you want surfaced whenever it shows up
- Another recurring interest
- A field you're learning about

## Tools I use
- Languages and frameworks in your daily stack
- Editors, CLIs, services you rely on

## Deprioritize
- Topics you want filtered out ("celebrity tech news", "crypto", etc.)

## Surface daily
- Specific things the brief should never miss (e.g. "new releases of library X")
